cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST

The paper discusses methods for learning high-quality policies from data in a causal model, which involves machine learning and statistical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves causal inference and estimation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.ST (Statistics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mediation analysis and dynamic treatment regimes, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
